The vector formula_49 is an eigenvector of this matrix, where the eigenvalue formula_50 is a root of formula_5. Setting the initial values of the sequence equal to this vector produces a geometric sequence formula_52 which satisfies the recurrence. In the case of &quot;n&quot; distinct eigenvalues, an arbitrary solution formula_53 can be written as a linear combination of such geometric solutions, and the eigenvalues of largest complex norm give an asymptotic approximation.
